Implement in mock host VL-REGISTRY-WRITE VL-REGISTRY-DELETE VL-REGISTRY-READ VL-REGISTRY-DESCENDENTS.
They're specified to work on Windows, and on MacOS (using defaults, NSDefaults).


* Resolution (fix-vl-registry, 1.5.1)

New host-protocol generics HOST-REGISTRY-READ/-WRITE/-DELETE/
-DESCENDENTS; the mock host implements them over one persistent
per-user store — $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/clautolisp/registry.sexp, loaded on
first use, saved (prin1, readable strings) on every write/delete —
emulating both the Windows registry and macOS defaults. Keys are
case-insensitive backslash paths; nil value-name is the key's default
value; vl-registry-descendents returns immediate SUB-KEYS by default
and value names with the flag (the old session-hash returned value
names in both cases and never persisted). Builtins delegate to the
host; live CAD backends will map these to the real registry/defaults.


* RE-OPEN the issue.

vl-registry must be implemented in different ways on the 3 different target platforms.

- on windows #+(or (and sbcl win32)  (and ccl windows))

  vl-registry must be implemented exactly like autocad or bricscad
  implement it (as documented in the reference documentation) using the
  MS-Windows REGISTRY, thru the win32 quicklisp library system.

- on macos   #+darwin

  vl-registry must be implemented exactly like bricscad
  implements it (asf documented in the reference documentation) using the
  macOS defaults database. (NSDefaults)
 
- on unix    #+(and unix (not darwin))

  vl-registry can be implemented using $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/clautolisp/registry.sexp
  as described above.

* Status (fix-vl-registry-platforms, 1.5.7)

Platform backends implemented, feature-gated in
autolisp-mock-host/source/registry-api.lisp:

- windows: the real Windows registry through reg.exe (query/add/delete,
  /v NAME, /ve for the default value; sub-keys vs value names parsed
  from reg query). NOTE: the "win32" quicklisp library named in the
  re-open is NOT in the quicklisp dist (only cl-win32-errors); reg.exe
  is the stable documented interface present on every Windows — point
  at the exact FFI system and it can be swapped in.
- darwin: the macOS defaults database (NSUserDefaults) through
  /usr/bin/defaults, domain org.clautolisp.vl-registry, flat keys
  "REGPATH|VALUENAME" (BricsCAD-style plist mapping); enumeration via
  defaults export XML.
- unix (not darwin): the persistent sexp store (unchanged, tested).

REMAINS: verify on the Windows PC and on thalassa (macOS) — the linux
CI cannot exercise these paths. Issue stays open for that
verification (and the FFI-library decision).

* Verification jobs (fix-vl-registry-ci-verification, 1.5.8)

Manual CI jobs verify:vl-registry:macos / :windows run
scripts/verify-vl-registry.lisp on the native runners against the real
platform store (write/read, value-names, sub-keys, delete, cleanup).
Also fixed before any platform run: reg query echoes EXPANDED key
paths (HKEY_CURRENT_USER\..., not HKCU\...), so the sub-key parser now
collects the last path segment of each HKEY_ line instead of
prefix-matching the query key. Trigger the two jobs manually from a
pipeline to validate, then this issue can close.
